This paper deals with the creation of a dataset for semantic segmentation using Artificial Intelligence methods. The paper focuses on the performance of models based on the quality and quantity of data available. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of metrics to evaluate the performance of the models, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
